ural_normalized": false, "mention": "androstenedione", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9996490478515625, "span": {"begin": 517, "end": 532}}, {"id": ["mesh:D013739"], "is_neural_normalized": false, "mention": "testosterone", "obj": "drug", "prob": 0.9992596507072449, "span": {"begin": 566, "end": 578}}], "text": "The synthesis of testosterone from androstenedione by 17-beta-HSD is a well-studied and generally recognized process and the biological plausibility of the KER therefore is high.&nbsp;  17-beta-HSD is an enzyme responsible for synthesis of testosterone from androstenedione. There are several isoforms of the enzyme. 17-beta-HSD3 is the main enzyme in humans converting androstenedione to testosterone, whereas both 17-beta-HSD1 and 17-beta-HSD3 can perform the conversion in rodents. Reduced levels of the precursor androstenedione will result in reduced levels of testosterone (Fl&uuml;ck, 2017; Lawrence, 2022; Naamneh Elzenaty, 2022; O&rsquo;Donnell, 2022; Ye, 2014).", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:16:55 +0000 2026"}